text: The thing is even though as this is designed for children, the horrifc truth behind bullfighting, is that the bull is killed, by "spears stabbed in to the back of its neck". I should think that the Spanish would have outlawed this barbaric practice (its NOT sport, no more than fox hunting) the animal does not stand a chance, on the few occaisons that the "matador/murderer" (sic) loses, well I say on behalf of 1.2 billion Hindus Fair play. The most expensive seats are in the shade, so you do not get hot, watching this barbaric exhibition of torture by human beings, dressed up like a fucking chandelier and with a red rag. Personally I would have a pack of hungry, kevlar plated wolves; versus a spastic, narcissistic, spanish twat, that would be far more interesting. Matadors are fucking idiots, you can pull the culture card, but really are we more enlightened now? The Romans used Lions and other large preditors against gladiators, but that was 2 fucking thousand years ago.... They have moved on to being poor and stupid, and riding mopeds, the most dangerous thing there now is the traffic. The Spanish, are stupid in persisting in such a pointless endeavour, as it is we slaughter so many bulls for fucking Big Macs and have cut down swathes of the rain forest to do it... The film was average, the animation, not a spot on normal Blue Sky movies, such as ice age and few gags. Watch Coco, for a look in to a real tradition, the day of the dead.... much more fun and has a powerful message., about mexican culture. In this film there is no message, except that Bulls are abused and fought (then killed to a paying audience) for entertainment.
